description.description:
A description of the function. Used by the model to determine whether or not to
call the function.

name.description: The name of the function to call.

parameters.description: A JSON schema object describing the parameters of the function.

strict.description: Whether to enforce strict parameter validation. Default `true`.

type.description:
The type of the function tool. Always `function`.

This field can be elided, and will marshal its zero value as "function".

gid.description:
Gid is the primary group ID.
On POSIX systems, this is a decimal number representing the gid.
On Windows, this is a SID in a string format.
On Plan 9, this is the contents of /dev/user.

homeDir.description: HomeDir is the path to the user's home directory (if they have one).

name.description:
Name is the user's real or display name.
It might be blank.
On POSIX systems, this is the first (or only) entry in the GECOS field
list.
On Windows, this is the user's display name.
On Plan 9, this is the contents of /dev/user.

uid.description:
Uid is the user ID.
On POSIX systems, this is a decimal number representing the uid.
On Windows, this is a security identifier (SID) in a string format.
On Plan 9, this is the contents of /dev/user.
